ll. 167—8. Iasius pater: pateris a title of dignity (cp. 1. 35 n) and need not imply that Iasius was the father of Dardanus. According to one legend, Dardanus and Iasius were brothers, and so Virgil may have thought himself justified in attributing the foundation of Troy to both, although the general belief was that Dardanus settled in Phrygia (where according to the legend followed by Virg. in l. 108, he married the daughter of Teucer) and larius in Samothrace.
